'''''Treasure Hunt''''' is a 1994 Hong Kong [[action comedy]] and [[romantic fantasy]] film written and directed by [[Jeffrey Lau]] and starring [[Chow Yun-fat]] and [[Jacklyn Wu]].

==Plot==
[[Chinese American]] [[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] operative Jeffrey Cheung Ching ([[Chow Yun-fat]]) was ordered to escort a [[China|Chinese]] national treasure to the [[United States]]. Cheung goes from America to [[Beijing]] where he stays at the [[Shaolin temple]]. There, he encounters conflicts due to culture barriers and different life habits. However, he became friends with Abbot Hung Chi ([[Gordon Liu]]) and a seven-year-old monk Grasshopper (Choi Yue). Cheung is later surprised to find out that the so-called national treasure is a [[parapsychology|para psychological]] girl named Siu-ching ([[Jacklyn Wu]]). During the process of exposing the evil sinister, Cheung and Ching develop a romance.

